    "These specialized systems, typically optical, utilize multiple cameras [112] or sensors [99] to meticulously track markers or objects within a designated area.",
    "They prove especially valuable in environments with low SLAM accuracy or where GPS signals are unavailable.",
    "Due to their firmly established precision in both temporal and spatial dimensions, tracking systems become a reliable reference for ground truth in controlled setups.The Ground Control Points (GCP) method constitutes the fourth approach.",
    "This method utilizes specific ground points with known and precise geographical locations, often established using total stations.",
    "These GCPs are frequently employed to guarantee accurate positioning and alignment."
